title: For Sale:  1943 HUNGARIAN FEMARU 37M, .380 acp
postcontent: Super Rare 1943 Hungarian Femaru 37M (Femaru-Fegyver Es Gepgyar R.T. 37M). WWII Era Issued Pistol. Used by German and Hungarian Military. Made in Budapest, Hungary. Chambered in 9mm Kurtz (.380 acp).This pistol was designed by Frommer, a prominent Hungarian gun manufactrer in Budapest, Hungary and he produced weapons for the Hungarian Army.  In 1929 Frommer originally produced the 29M which was superceded in 1937 by the 37M.  It is styled after the proven design of the Colt 1911 as most manufacturers did at that time.  This pistol was made in Budapest, Hungary in 1943 was used by the Hungarian Army until Nazi Germany occupied Hungary and renamed it 'Pistole 37(u)', the lower case (u) was used to signify it's Hungarian origin.  As you can see from the photos showing the serial number, this pistol is nearly 75 years old.  The caliber is .380 acp and was referred to as 9mm Kurz.The .380 barrel is interchangeable with the 7.65 (.32acp) barrel as is the mag.  The 7.65 was produced by Femaru for the German Luftwaffe after occupation and an additional safety was installed at the rear of the slide.  The only safety on an original Femaru 37M, such as this one, is a grip safety.I HAVE MORE PHOTOS. Email or message me and I'll send you the photos. The photos exceed the Up-Load Limit for Armslist, so I can only post the one photo.I WILL TAKE THE FOLLOWING IN TRADE, +/- Cash where necessary:1. title: For Sale:  Taurus pt1911
postcontent: The Taurus pt1911 is a clone of the Us Military 1911, single action, recoil operated pistol. It was designed and manufactured by Taurus in Porto Alegre Brazil and distributed in the US by Taurus USA. Announced at the 2005 Shot Show, it was released to the consumer market in the fall of 2005.The PT1911 differs from its many competitors in the 1911-style market in that the basic model offers a package of features found on top-end models from more expensive semi-custom pistol manufacturers such as Springfield Armory, Para-Ordnance, Kimber Manufacturing at a significantly lower cost.   Featuring a forged steel frame and slide, the PT1911 was originally marketed with a blued carbon steel finish, but as of late 2007 a stainless steel version was released. The standard PT1911 is hand-fit in the Taurus factory and includes popular combat and competition custom features such as a "Beavertail" grip safety with memory groove, extended ambidextrous thumb safety and slide stop controls, lowered and flared ejection port, frame checkering, and other niceties unusual for a pistol of its price range.

postcontent:
HK MP5 HK94 SP89 Factory Mag Magazine 9mm 30rd
H&K GERMAN Factory original HK 9mm 30 round magazine for the MP5 SP89 HK94 and other 9mm clones.
This is ORIGINAL H&K Factory German made Magazine  30rd.  These are not the Korean Made under License by H&K you see advertised on others auction listings.  These are NOT the Turkish made which are marked MKE. And these are NOT the British Aerospace mags are marked EN.   This magazine is ORIGIANL GEMAAN H&K FACTORY MADE.  Whether you buy ours or not Please be careful  I have read through a lot of auctions and they state Factory or H&K OEM and they are NOT GERMAN made.   If you are looking for the Great German Craftsmanship, you want these mags.  
Just for your information when purchasing H&K MP% HK 94 magazines  here is a brief list of things you should know, Some of the H&K listed mags are made in Pakistan, POF, Pakistani Ordnance Factory mags were not marked other than being stamped 9 x 19. Later Paki mags were stamped POF and 9x19 on the body.    Turkish H&K mags are maked MKE and 9x 19 and British Aerospace H&K mags are marked EN if I remember correctly. Korean, made in Korea by a military NATO approved manufacturer, sometimes marked ATI or KC or they have a numerical date code on them.  HK NEVER produced any 40rd straight or curved mags for the MP5
 
Note the picture with the “Made in Germany” imprinted
These mags were made in 1996 based on the date code and therefore have the L/E Govt makings. They are LEGAL to buy and posses by ANYONE since the expiration of the Federal Hi cap mag ban in 2004.  Blue Steel and Stainless Steel Follower. These are the best H&K mags on the market. Not only do they function flawlessly, they have a Collector value with the L/E Govt imprint on them.  there were only a finite / limited number of these produced and they are no longer in production (1994-2004). title: For Sale:  PVS-14 Gen 3 Autogated Night Vision Monocular w/ accessories
postcontent: This is a PVS-14 Gen 3 night vision monocular in lightly used condition. It produces an exceptionally clear image with virtually no spots or blemishes, meaning it was probably hand selected for tube quality (it is within specs for even a new $3600 unit to have a few black spots around the edge of the image, which this one doesn't have). This unit appears to be autogated -- it dims when pointed at a bright light, which prevents tube damage. This unit comes with a dual battery housing, which gives it a longer battery life than the single battery units (65 hours continual use as opposed to 40 hours). It takes AA batteries.I was told by the previous owner that this unit has only been used for a few hours... the condition of the unit and quality of the image is definitely consistent with that. I have used it less than an hour myself, so it has the vast majority of its service life left, and will provide many good years of service.I was also told by the previous owner that this unit has an Omni tube, meaning it is mil spec and that unlike the ITT/Pinnacle tubes, it is rated for .308 recoil.It comes with the attached lens cover/pinhole lens (for testing the unit in regular lighting), a J-arm mount (used for mounting to a helmet or "skull crusher" headgear), as well as a weapon mount, for mounting the unit on a Picatinny rail either behind or in front of AR-height optics. It works great behind my Aimpoint PRO or Comp M4. It also works great in front of a scope that can adjust down to 1x.Get this very clean Gen 3 night vision unit in great condition for over $1,000 less than a new one would cost, or for the same as you would pay for a Gen 2 unit, if you want to think of it that way. If you have never used Gen 3 night vision, let's just say it blows Gen 1 and Gen 2 out of the water in every possible way... it's not even close. A unit like this gives you a massively unfair advantage in any low light situation.I would take $2200 OBO.I am willing to ship, with the buyer paying.Also, not interested in trading.
